text: Sylvère Maes (born August 27, 1909 in Zevekote – died December 5, 1966 in Ostend) was a Belgian cyclist, who is most famous for winning the Tour de France in 1936 and 1939. ==References== * Profile Category:1909 births Category:1966 deaths Category:Belgian cyclists Category:People from West Flanders Category:Tour de France winners
title: Sylvère Maes
